ment. The project is expected to last approximately 2-3 weeks, with regular feedback loops to ensure that both parties are aligned on the progress and any issues that may arise.\n\n\n# 6. Required Contribution From Client\ndd must provide the following:\n- Technical resources: Access to their dev/test environment and technical expertise.\n- Diagrams or architectural artifacts: Current architecture diagrams and any relevant technical documentation.\n- Access to dev/test environment: dd will provide Oracle with access to their dev/test environment for the duration of the project.\n\n\n# 7. Expected Deliverables From Oracle ISV Labs\nOracle will deliver the following:\n- Terraform modules for automating the deployment of the application on OCI.\n- Target architecture in OCI, including a detailed design document.\n- Technical documentation, including setup guides and troubleshooting tips.\n- CI/CD integration examples, if relevant to the project.\n\n\n# 8. Cloud Environment Used\nThe proof of concept (PoC) will run in a **Temporary Test Tenancy** provided by Oracle for the duration of the project.\n\n\n# 9. dd Company Profile\n- Legal Name: **dd Corporation**\n- Country of Operations: **USA**\n- Company Overview: **dd is a leading provider of technology solutions, focusing on innovation and customer satisfaction.**\n- Website link: **https://www.dd.com**\n\n\n# 10. In-Scope Application: ddd\n- Application Name: **ddd**\n- General Description: **ddd is a cloud-native application designed for real-time data processing and analytics.**\n- Key Technologies: **Kubernetes, PostgreSQL, Apache Kafka**\n- Current Hosting: **On-premises**\n\n\n# 11. Project Overview\n- **Validation Summary**: The objective of this project is to validate the deployment of ddd on Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI), ensuring its compatibility and performance on the OCI platform.\n- Desired outcome:\n  - Successful deployment of ddd on OCI.\n  - Verification of the application's performance and scalability.\n  - Identification of any potential issues or areas for improvement.\n- Scope boundaries:\n  - The project will focus on the deployment and validation of ddd on OCI.\n  - It will not include the migration of production workloads or the setup of production environments.\n- Joint goals:\n  - To ensure a smooth and successful deployment of ddd on OCI.\n  - To identify and address any technical or operational challenges that may arise during the project.\n\n\n# 12. Scope\n- **In-Scope Items**:\n  - PostgreSQL setup and configuration.\n  - Apache Kafka integration for real-time data processing.\n  - Deployment of ddd on OCI using Terraform.\n- **Out-of-Scope Items**:\n  - Production migration.\n  - Licensing setup.\n  - SLA support.\n- Validation boundaries and limitations: The validation will be conducted within the temporary test tenancy provided by Oracle and will be limited to the deployment and performance testing of ddd on OCI.\n\n\n# 13. Major Project Milestones\n| Milestone                         | Target Date | Completed | Comments                 |\n|----------------------------------|-------------|-----------|--------------------------|\n| Kickoff with Cloud Architect     | 2024-09-20  |           |                          |\n| OCI Network Setup                | 2024-09-25  |           |                          |\n| Terraform Code Finalization      | 2024-10-01  |           |                          |\n| Application Deployment in OCI    | 2024-10-05  |           |                          |\n| Final Validation & Review        | 2024-10-15  |           |                          |\n\n\n# 14. Acceptance Criteria\n| Capability/Metric                                | Acceptance Criteria                                                       | Status  |\n|--------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------|---------|\n| Kubernetes Deployment                            | ddd runs 