: 1 instance with 2 CPUs and 16 GB RAM.\n  - IAM Policies: Custom policy for database administration.\n- **OKE Node Pools config**: 2 node pools with different instance types for workload segregation.\n- **PostgreSQL shape, version**: 2 CPUs, 16 GB RAM, PostgreSQL 13.\n- **Streaming configuration**: 3 brokers, 3 partitions, with a replication factor of 3.\n\n\n# 18. Security Considerations\n- **IAM Policy examples**: Custom policies for OKE cluster administration, streaming administration, and database administration.\n- **NSG configuration**: Inbound rules for OKE node ports, outbound rules for PostgreSQL and streaming services.\n- **Data encryption approach**: Encryption in transit using SSL/TLS, encryption at rest using Oracle-managed keys.\n- **Audit logs or Logging Analytics setup**: OCI Logging Analytics for log collection and analysis.\n\n\n# 19. High Availability & Disaster Recovery\n- **OKE NodePools across ADs**: Node pools will be spread across 2 availability domains for high availability.\n- **PostgreSQL HA with replica**: 1 primary instance and 1 standby instance in a different AD.\n- **Object Storage cross-region replication**: Not applicable for this project.\n- **DNS failover via Traffic Management**: Not applicable for this project.\n- **DR architecture summary**: The disaster recovery architecture will focus on high availability within the region, with node pools and PostgreSQL instances spread across multiple availability domains.\n\n\n# 20. Closing Feedback\n- **Oracle**: \n- **dd**: \n\n\n# 21. Sign-Off Section\n- **Client Acceptance**: \n- **Oracle Confirmation**: \n- **Final next steps**: \n- **Version tagging**: 0.1\n---\n\n"
