g                           | Basic metrics visible in OCI Monitoring dashboard.           | TBD        |  \n| Security                             | IAM + NSG + Encryption in Transit & At Rest implemented.     | TBD        |  \n\n---\n\n### **15. Current State Architecture**  \n- **Diagram Description**: On-premises setup with Kubernetes clusters, PostgreSQL database, and manual deployment pipelines.  \n- **Tech Stack**: Docker, Helm, PostgreSQL 12, Java 11.  \n- **Known Issues**: Manual scaling, slow database performance, and lack of automated monitoring.  \n\n---\n\n### **16. Target OCI Architecture**  \n- **Service Mapping**:  \n  | **Current Component** | **OCI Service**          |  \n  |-----------------------|--------------------------|  \n  | Kubernetes            | Oracle Kubernetes Engine (OKE) |  \n  | PostgreSQL            | Autonomous Database      |  \n  | Monitoring            | OCI Monitoring           |  \n\n- **Component Interaction**:  \n  - XRP containers deployed on OKE.  \n  - AutonomousDB handles all database operations.  \n  - OCI Monitoring tracks application and infrastructure metrics.  \n\n- **Diagram Placeholder**: Layout includes OKE clusters, AutonomousDB, and OCI Monitoring interconnected via OCI Networking.  \n\n---\n\n### **17. Implementation Details and Configuration Settings**  \n**OKE**:  \n- **Node Pools**: 3 nodes per pool, VM.Standard2.4 shape.  \n- **IAM Policies**: Restrict access to OKE cluster.  \n- **Helm Usage**: Deploy XRP using Helm charts.  \n\n**AutonomousDB**:  \n- **Shape**: VM.Standard.E4.16GB.  \n- **Version**: PostgreSQL 12.  \n- **Backup**: Daily backups to OCI Object Storage.  \n\n**Security**:  \n- **NSG**: Restrict inbound traffic to necessary ports.  \n- **Encryption**: Data encrypted in transit (TLS) and at rest.  \n\n---\n\n### **18. Security Considerations**  \n- **IAM Policies**: Least privilege access for OKE and AutonomousDB.  \n- **NSG Configuration**: Allow only necessary ports (e.g., 443, 5432).  \n