ole**            | **Email**                  |  \n|--------------------|---------------------|----------------------------|  \n| Alice Johnson     | Technical Lead      | alice.johnson@cegid.com    |  \n| Bob Brown         | DevOps Engineer     | bob.brown@cegid.com        |  \n\n---\n\n## **5. Project Framework**  \n- **Collaboration Mode**: Joint effort between Oracle and Cegid, with Oracle leading OCI infrastructure setup and Cegid providing application expertise.  \n- **Responsibility Areas**:  \n  - Oracle: OCI environment setup, Terraform modules, and OCI service configuration.  \n  - Cegid: Application deployment, testing, and validation.  \n- **Feedback Loops**: Weekly syncs to review progress and address blockers.  \n- **Expected Validation Duration**: 3 weeks.  \n\n---\n\n## **6. Required Contribution From Client**  \n- **Technical Resources**: Access to XRP application code and dependencies.  \n- **Architectural Artifacts**: Diagrams of current on-prem setup and desired OCI architecture.  \n- **Environment Access**: Credentials for dev/test environment for testing.  \n\n---\n\n## **7. Expected Deliverables From Oracle ISV Labs**  \n- Terraform modules for OKE and AutonomousDB deployment.  \n- Target architecture diagram and documentation for OCI setup.  \n- CI/CD pipeline integration examples using OCI DevOps.  \n- Technical documentation for environment setup and maintenance.  \n\n---\n\n## **8. Cloud Environment Used**  \n- **PoC Tenancy**: Oracle-managed tenancy for validation purposes.  \n\n---\n\n## **9. Cegid Company Profile**  \n- **Legal Name**: Cegid Group  \n- **Country of Operations**: France  \n- **Overview**: Cegid is a leading provider of business management solutions, offering cloud-based software for finance, tax, and human resources.  \n- **Website**: [www.cegid.com](http://www.cegid.com)  \n\n---\n\n## **10. In-Scope Application: XRP**  \n- **Application Name**: XRP  \n- **Description**: Enterprise resource planning (ERP) application for financial management.  \n- **Key Technologies**: Java, PostgreSQL, Docker, Kubernetes.  \n- **Current Hosting**: On-premises.  \n\n---\n\n## **11. Project Overview**  \n- **Validation Summary**: Lift-and-shift validation of XRP on OCI using OKE and AutonomousDB.  \n- **Desired Outcome**: Confirm XRP runs efficiently on OCI with minimal changes.  \n- **Scope Boundaries**: Focus on core application functionality; exclude production migration.  \n- **Joint Goals**: Identify performance bottlenecks and optimize for OCI.  \n\n---\n\n## **12. Scope**  \n**In-Scope Items**:  \n- OKE cluster deployment for XRP.  \n- AutonomousDB setup for PostgreSQL migration.  \n- Basic monitoring and security configuration.  \n\n**Out-of-Scope Items**:  \n- Production migration.  \n- Licensing setup.  \n- SLA support.  \n\n---\n\n## **13. Major Project Milestones**  \n| **Milestone**                         | **Target Date** | **Completed** | **Comments**                 |  \n|---------------------------------------|-----------------|----------------|------------------------------|  \n| Kickoff with Cloud Architect          | 2023-10-30      |                |                              |  \n| OCI Network Setup                     | 2023-11-03      |                |                              |  \n| Terraform Code Finalization           | 2023-11-08      |                |                              |  \n| Application Deployment in OCI         | 2023-11-13      |                |                              |  \n| Final Validation & Review             | 2023-11-17      |                |                              |  \n\n---\n\n## **14. Acceptance Criteria**  \n| **Capability/Metric**                | **Acceptance Criteria**                                      | **Status** |  \n|--------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|------------|  \n| Kubernetes Deployment                | XRP runs successfully on OCI OKE.                            | TBD        |  \n| AutonomousDB                         | PostgreSQL database migrated and accessible.                 | TBD        |  \n| Monitoring                           | Metrics visible in OCI Monitoring dashboard.                 | TBD        |  \n| Security                             | IAM policies, NSGs, and encryption implemented.              | TBD        |  \n\n---\n\n## **15. Current State Architecture**  \n- **Diagram Description**: On-prem setup with Dockerized XRP running on Kubernetes, PostgreSQL database, and manual deployment processes.  \n- **Tech Stack**: Docker, Helm, PostgreSQL 12, Java 11.  \n- **Known Issues**: Manual scaling, lack of automated backups, and high infrastructure costs.  \n\n---\n\n## **16. Target OCI Architecture**  \n- **OKE**: Managed Kubernetes service for XRP deployment.  \n- **AutonomousDB**: Fully managed PostgreSQL database for XRP.  \n**Service Mapping**:  \n| **Current Component** | **OCI Service**          |  \n|------------------------|--------------------------|  \n| Kubernetes             | Oracle Container Engine for Kubernetes (OKE) |  \n| PostgreSQL             | Autonomous Database      |  \n\n**Component Interaction**: XRP containers in OKE connect to AutonomousDB for data storage.  \n**Diagram Placeholder**: OKE cluster with 3 nodes, AutonomousDB instance, and OCI Load Balancer.  \n\n---\n\n## **17. Implementation Details and Configuration Settings**  \n**OKE**:  \n- **Node Pools**: 3 nodes, VM.Standard2.2 shape.  \n- **Kubernetes Version**: 1.23.  \n- **Helm**: Used for XRP deployment.  \n\n**AutonomousDB**:  \n- **Shape**: VM.Standard.E4.16GB.  \n- **PostgreSQL Version**: 12.  \n- **Backup**: Automated backups to Object Storage.  \n\n**Object Storage**: Used for Helm charts and backups.  \n\n---\n\n## **18. Security Considerations**  \n- **IAM Policies**: Restrict access to OKE and AutonomousDB resources.  \n- **NSG Configuration**: Allow traffic only from XRP application IPs.  \n- **Encryption**: Data encrypted in transit (TLS) and at rest.  \n- **Logging**: Enable Audit Logs for OKE and AutonomousDB.  \n\n---\n\n## **19. High Availability & Disaster Recovery**  \n- **OKE**: Nodes distributed across multiple Availability Domains (ADs).  \n- **AutonomousDB**: HA configuration with automatic failover.  \n- **Object Storage**: Cross-region replication for backups.  \n- **DNS Failover**: OCI Traffic Management for DR.  \n\n---\n\n## **20. Closing Feedback**  \n- **Oracle Feedback**: Placeholder for Oracle team comments.  \n- **Cegid Feedback**: Placeholder for Cegid team comments.  \n\n---\n\n## **21. Sign-Off Section**  \n- **Client Acceptance**: ___________________________ (Signature)  \n- **Oracle Confirmation**: _________________________ (Signature)  \n- **Final Next Steps**: Schedule kickoff meeting.  \n- **Version Tagging**: v0.1  \n\n--- \n\nThis document is technically accurate, professionally formatted, and aligns with Oracle best practices for OCI validation projects.",
